y a clean diesel engine capable of running on renewable fuels the doe funding will cover up to half of the projects cost and will be provided over three years subject to annual appropriations estar electric vanedit the estar was an allelectric van production began in march  and first deliveries began two months later via its workhorse group division the technology used in estar was licensed to navistar in  in a joint venture with modec and navistar bought the intellectual property rights from the modecs bankruptcy administrators in  the introduction of the estar was supported by a us million us department of energy stimulus grant under the  american recovery and reinvestment act the estar had a  lb  kg payload capacity available with a  or foot cargo box the vehicle was powered by a  kw  hp electric motor powered by an kwhr lithiumion battery pack supplied by a systems and also used regenerative braking the electric van had a range of  mi  km and a full charge took between  and  hours by may  the estar had received us environmental protection agency epa and carb certifications the estar also met all federal motor vehicle safety standards fmvss the first vans were delivered in may  to fedex express for use in los angeles other customers included pacific gas and electric company pge the cocacola company and canada post the estar had a price of us navistar discontinued the estar van in march  as part of a corporate restructuring plan to focus on current profitability criticismedit in december  the nonpartisan organization public campaign criticized navistar international for spending  million on lobbying and not paying any taxes during  instead getting  million in tax rebates despite making a profit of  million and increasing executive pay by  on jan   navistar financial said it would restate financial statements for fiscal years  and  and the first three quarters of fiscal  because it did not take into consideration potential changes to future income on april   navist